
[1]shirt

   SHIRT, n. shurt. [L. curtus.] A loose garment of linen, cotton or other
   material, worn by men and boys next the body.

   It is folly for a nation to export beef and linen, while a great part
   of the peaple are obliged to subsist on potatoes, and have no shirts to
   wear. A.M.

   SHIRT, v.t. shurt.

   1. To cover or clothe, as with a shirt.

   2. To change the shirt and put on a clean one.
